<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a108c82-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s2903"><num value="2903">§ 2903.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise requires:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a108c83-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s2903/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The term “Board” means the Climate Program Policy Board.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a108c84-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s2903/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> The term “Office” means the National Climate Program Office.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a108c85-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s2903/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> The term “Program” means the National Climate Program.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a108c86-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s2903/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Commerce.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a108c87-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/367/s4">Pub. L. 95–367, § 4</ref>, <date date="1978-09-17">Sept. 17, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/601">92 Stat. 601</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/272/tVI/s6084/a">Pub. L. 99–272, title VI, § 6084(a)</ref>, <date date="1986-04-07">Apr. 7, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/136">100 Stat. 136</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a108c88-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a108c89-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a108c8a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1986—<ref href="/us/pl/99/272">Pub. L. 99–272</ref> added par. (1) and redesignated former pars. (1) to (3) as (2) to (4), respectively.</p>
</note>
</notes>
